# Echothink-Patch: 0015-side-panel-mode-selector
# Title: Persist the Echothink Side Panel mode selector
# Area: extension
# Depends-On: echothink/0004-bundled-workspace-extension.patch, echothink/0014-side-panel-container.patch
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The bundled workspace side panel needs a local profile-scoped mode selector before service-rendered Chat or Workspace Context content exists. Keeping the selector in the MV3 extension uses extension storage and avoids native Chromium state plumbing.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: extension (local sidepanel.html/sidepanel.js UI and chrome.storage.local)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.html, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.css, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.js
# Rebase-Risk: low (updates only bundled extension resource files added by echothink/0004)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches, then echothink/0001..0005 and later tail patches including echothink/0014 and this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178; launch a fresh profile, switch between Chat and Workspace Context in the Side Panel, restart, and verify the selected mode persists in that profile.
#
# Notes:
# - This patch supports exactly the Alpha modes `chat` and
#   `workspace_context`; unsupported stored values fall back to `chat`.
# - Mode state is stored only in chrome.storage.local, making it local to the
#   extension install/profile. The patch does not use sync storage, remote
#   account state, backend services, privileged bridges, or broader extension
#   permissions.

